            "id": "15719048",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=Naganarasimha",
              "name": "Naganarasimha",
              "key": "naganarasimha",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Naganarasimha G R",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "body": "Yes [~templedf], we started of with YARN-4494 as the base idea, with focus of \"fast recovery using async calls and multiple threads\". We have come up less modifications on the zoo keeper structure too. We have incorporated \"async calls and multiple threads\" and tested extensively in our test clusters and results seem to be promising and as [~varun_saxena] mentioned, we will come up design doc and initial patch.\nWe also wanted to incorporate YARN-2962 to have it under one umbrella, as its important for large clusters. ",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=Naganarasimha",
              "name": "Naganarasimha",
              "key": "naganarasimha",
