          "displayName": "zhangyubiao",
          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "Asia/Hong_Kong"
        },
        "body": "[~templedf], is it zookeeper is the best way to store the app state? is it can improve good enough performance to the large cluster to recovery apps?\n as we [~tangshangwen] [~zhengchenyu] see in  http://www.slideshare.net/arinto/next-generation-hadoop-high-availability-for-yarn.\n it seem like that zookeeper is not the best way to store the app state.\n[~Naganarasimha]  [~varun_saxena]  [~rohithsharma]",
        "updateAuthor": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=piaoyu+zhang",
          "name": "piaoyu zhang",
          "key": "piaoyu zhang",
          "avatarUrls": {
            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=piaoyu+zhang&avatarId=21665",
            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=piaoyu+zhang&avatarId=21665",
            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=piaoyu+zhang&avatarId=21665",
            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=piaoyu+zhang&avatarId=21665"
